      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ranged Tactics Toolbox pg. 33</em>, <em>PRPG Core Rulebook pg. 143</em>, <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 21</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 5 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 2 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d3 (small), 1d4 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x2; <strong>Range</strong> 10 ft.; <strong>Type</strong> B; <strong>Special</strong> nonlethal, trip</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Ranged; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Thrown</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>A bolas is a pair of wooden, stone, or metal weights connected by a thin rope or cord. You can whirl and throw this weapon to make a ranged trip attack against an opponent. You can't be tripped during your own trip attempt when using a bolas.</p>",
